# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in only the providers you have set up.
# Every var below is OPTIONAL — anything missing is silently skipped at runtime.

# --- Firebase (Analytics + per-excuse Firestore logging) ---
# Free Spark tier. One Firebase project gives you:
#   - Visitor / session / retention analytics (GA4) → needs Google Analytics enabled
#   - Per-excuse copy/share rows in Firestore → needs Firestore + Anonymous Auth
#
# Setup (in Firebase Console):
#   1. Project Settings → ⚙ → Integrations → Google Analytics → Enable, pick a GA account
#   2. Authentication → Sign-in method → Anonymous → Enable
#   3. Firestore Database → Create database → production mode → choose region
#   4. Firestore → Rules → paste:
#
#        rules_version = '2';
#        service cloud.firestore {
#          match /databases/{database}/documents {
#            match /events/{doc} {
#              allow create: if request.auth != null;
#              allow read, update, delete: if false;
#            }
#          }
#        }
#
#   5. Authentication → Settings → Authorized domains → add `whoopsie.aks1n3d.com`
#   6. Project Settings → General → Your apps → Web app → copy these values:
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=

# --- GlitchTip (error tracking, Sentry-compatible) ---
# Free at https://app.glitchtip.com (or self-hosted). Project Settings → Client Keys (DSN).
VITE_GLITCHTIP_DSN=
